A California Safety Commissioner said, "I've been wandering around San Francisco and it's like  the blind man trying to feel an elephant.
We're just now figuring out bits and pieces of this  disaster."
A schoolteacher said, "Usually earthquakes pass but this one went on and on.
It just wouldn't  stop, it was very, very bad."
A woman driving toward San Francisco said, "At first I thought the smoke was fog.
Then I could  see a ball of flame."
A reporter covering the World Series at Candlestick Park noted, "The upper deck was absolutely  shaking, the light stanchions were blowing back and forth."
